| **Timer Misalignment** | No timers; synchronous batch completion | Ensures all records processed before Lambda terminates |
| **Full Materialization** | Streaming `IEnumerable` processing where possible | Reduces memory allocation overhead |

## Summary

**Primary finding**: The existing batch processing pipeline is unsuitable for micro-batching due to high per-invocation initialization costs from reflection-based strategy discovery, TPL Dataflow setup overhead, and inefficient per-record S3 write patterns. These architectural decisions were appropriate for hourly/daily batch jobs processing millions of records but create unacceptable latency for 30-60 second micro-batches with a 90-second SLA.

